[{"question":"Are they going to do that?","answer":"LUMENTHAL: I think that the issue remains a very open -- one in the minds of many of my colleagues because they are hearing from their constituents that we really need to do something about gun violence.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":50,"aSentId":51},{"question":"Where does that leave the president?","answer":"Well, the NRA never misses an opportunity to miss an opportunity.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":71,"aSentId":72},{"question":"And what did you agree with him about?","answer":"Nothing.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":110,"aSentId":111},{"question":"You don\u0027t agree with universal background checks for gun sales?","answer":"In French, back to the Bill of Rights.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":118,"aSentId":119},{"question":"You don\u0027t agree with that?","answer":"Infringe on my rights.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":121,"aSentId":122},{"question":"What possible infringement of your rights is it as a member of the American society if you want to buy a gun that are background checked?","answer":"Well, here\u0027s the deal.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"Would you cap ammunition magazines to a 10-round limit?","answer":"No.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":149,"aSentId":150},{"question":"Why?","answer":"Because it doesn\u0027t say so in the Constitution.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":151,"aSentId":152},{"question":"Piers, more importantly where does it say I cannot?","answer":"Right.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":155,"aSentId":156},{"question":"So where\u0027s the limit?","answer":"Well, there is not because it doesn\u0027t say it.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":157,"aSentId":158},{"question":"Do you believe the Second Amendment gives you, Scottie Hughes, the right to have a tank?","answer":"You know what, honestly, I don\u0027t see bullet points in the Constitution, sure.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":172,"aSentId":173},{"question":"Do you feel you have the right to have a tank?","answer":"That\u0027s an interesting question, Piers.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":179,"aSentId":180},{"question":"How can this be a sensible conversation?","answer":"No -- listen, listen, listen, listen -- no, listen.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":183,"aSentId":184},{"question":"-- say you want the right to a tank?","answer":"I haven\u0027t even said anything yet.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":190,"aSentId":191},{"question":"Do you think you should have the right to have a tank under the Second Amendment?","answer":"I think the Constitution is clear and it says that we have a right to bear arms under the definition of arms.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":208,"aSentId":209},{"question":"Does that include a tank?","answer":"If that is how arms is defined, I\u0027m going to let you draw your conclusions on that.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":211,"aSentId":212},{"question":"So have you started using the term -- have you stopped using the term assault rifle?","answer":"Dana, Dana, Dana -- I\u0027ll come to that in a moment.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":220,"aSentId":221},{"question":"The Second Amendment gives you, as Scottie believes, the right to have a tank?","answer":"I believe that the Second Amendment gives us all the right to bear arms.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":228,"aSentId":229},{"question":"Does that include a tank?","answer":"If that\u0027s how -- if it falls under the definition of firearms.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":231,"aSentId":232},{"question":"Do you think it does?","answer":"I -- if it falls under the definition of firearms.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":233,"aSentId":234},{"question":"Do you think it does, Dana?","answer":"If I say so, you\u0027re going to -- you\u0027re going to fire back.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":235,"aSentId":236},{"question":"Do you think it does?","answer":"And accuse me about my interpretation.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":237,"aSentId":238},{"question":"Does the -- does your personal interpretation of the Second Amendment include your right to have a tank?","answer":"My personal interpretation of the Second Amendment isn\u0027t a personal interpretation.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":250,"aSentId":251},{"question":"Does that include a tank?","answer":"If it falls under the definition of firearms, Piers.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":257,"aSentId":258},{"question":"When is the last time you heard somebody want a tank and buy a tank?","answer":"Scottie has --","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"So you\u0027re an expert?","answer":"Well, my brother is, yes.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":316,"aSentId":317},{"question":"You don\u0027t dispute that?","answer":"And Columbine happened, and Columbine happened after that.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":363,"aSentId":364},{"question":"Do you dispute that it was banned?","answer":"And Columbine happened after that.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":367,"aSentId":368},{"question":"Why was it banned then under the 1994 assault weapons ban?","answer":"Because people don\u0027t like scary-looking guns.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"When is the last time you heard a crime done by one of those people?","answer":"OK, Dana Loesch, let\u0027s ask you that question which is about the magazine clips.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":407,"aSentId":408},{"question":"Do you think that there is any reason why any civilian needs a magazine -- or magazine drums at it is now, over 10-round limit or more?","answer":"I think that there exist reasons that exactly why we should have more than.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":409,"aSentId":410},{"question":"What is the point of that anecdote?","answer":"And also, and also, Piers --","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":416,"aSentId":417},{"question":"But Dana, why do you tell that story?","answer":"Well, because it\u0027s to highlight that if someone has a firearm and they\u0027re able to defend themselves --","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":418,"aSentId":419},{"question":"Have you seen the video?","answer":"Or -- I\u0027ve seen -- I actually have screen shots of it.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":421,"aSentId":422},{"question":"So that young man should have shot those people?","answer":"I\u0027m not saying that.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":443,"aSentId":444},{"question":"What are you saying then?","answer":"There are instances where there is more than one people, more than one person coming at you.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":446,"aSentId":447},{"question":"Have you ever fired one?","answer":"I haven\u0027t fired one.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"Why would anybody need that?","answer":"Well, first and foremost, if you\u0027ve never fired an AR- 15, as a woman, who also has self-defense -- has -- uses guns for self-defense and likes to know that I have that security they\u0027re a lot easier to fire than other rifles simply because of the recoil.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":480,"aSentId":481},{"question":"Or one of these high-capacity magazines?","answer":"Piers, how are law-abiding --","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":506,"aSentId":507},{"question":"Why should I be punished?","answer":"James Holmes was a law-abiding citizen.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":521,"aSentId":522},{"question":"Do you realize that there are laws that have been passed to incentivize states recording these people?","answer":"Scottie said early that she --","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":565,"aSentId":566},{"question":"Is there anything there you agreed with?","answer":"You know, I\u0027m really -- because I think that he was moved by what happened at Newtown, which I think anybody would have been.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":572,"aSentId":573},{"question":"Was there anything you agreed within the president\u0027s proposals?","answer":"No.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":575,"aSentId":576},{"question":"You know something?","answer":"-- I would have liked to have the mother from Georgia that sat there.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":580,"aSentId":581},{"question":"How can he do it?","answer":"Well, he has this stuff he chose precisely because he doesn\u0027t have to send it through the Senate or the House.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":621,"aSentId":622},{"question":"Well, what the bloody hell are they?","answer":"I grew up on a farm in a world surrounded by guns.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":654,"aSentId":655},{"question":"What are you left with?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s fun.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":661,"aSentId":662},{"question":"Is fun a good enough excuse?","answer":"No.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":664,"aSentId":665},{"question":"We know that three Americans may be among the hostages, I think?","answer":"We know very little about this.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":672,"aSentId":673},{"question":"How are you doing?","answer":"I\u0027m good.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":700,"aSentId":701},{"question":"Thank you How are you?","answer":"I\u0027m feeling great.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":702,"aSentId":703},{"question":"What is your take on what was a very momentous day today for President Obama and his administration, and I think for America?","answer":"Well, look, I think this is a really polarizing issue.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":709,"aSentId":710},{"question":"Do you believe the Constitution gives you the right to have a tank?","answer":"Well, I think the Constitution -- when the Founding Fathers wrote the Constitution, I don\u0027t think they envisioned, you know, rapid-fire weapons or anything like that.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":718,"aSentId":719},{"question":"They couldn\u0027t find any common ground in anything?","answer":"But those are just two people.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":724,"aSentId":725},{"question":"Did you get to know him?","answer":"He basically, you know, asked me what the weather was going to be, and then kept moving.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":738,"aSentId":739},{"question":"What do you think of it?","answer":"Well, look --","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":744,"aSentId":745},{"question":"Do you feel like it\u0027s got you all energized again?","answer":"I think, look, we were always energized.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":818,"aSentId":819},{"question":"Your neck is disappearing, like the rest of you, at a rate -- you\u0027ve lost an unfeasible amount of wait, 350 pounds down to -- fighting wait now?","answer":"Right, 205.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":850,"aSentId":851},{"question":"Because you can have all the diets and things in the world, but until your head\u0027s right -- what are the things that you felt were most effective?","answer":"A, in this country, we need to cut back on portions.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":877,"aSentId":878},{"question":"Have you ever seen a happy runner?","answer":"Let me tell you about a high work out.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":905,"aSentId":906},{"question":"The White House incident, probably the most revolting story I\u0027ve ever heard on national television?","answer":"I am sure there is worse, but here is the deal.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":921,"aSentId":922},{"question":"Can we have you read the tease to the break, please?","answer":"All right.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":942,"aSentId":943},{"question":"In one word, what will the weather be like tomorrow?","answer":"It\u0027s going to be spectacular.","docId":"130116pmt","qSentId":953,"aSentId":954}]